      <p>
        Chinese words can be divided into two kinds.  The first kind is notional words and the second kind has a 
        purely grammatical purpose (function words). 
        Notional words can be divided into seven categories: nouns, verbs, auxiliary verbs, adjectives, numerals, 
        measure words, and pronouns.
        Chinese has a rich collection of measure words, one for each object and action.  Measure words 
        must be used and cannot be arbitrarily used.
      </p>
