        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">中心语</a>。
      </p>
      <p>
        When a noun is acting as the attributive it must be placed before the modified word.
        For example, in the sentence <a href='/word_detail.php?id=374' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'nín', 'you (formal)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">您</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=335' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yào', 'to want ')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">要</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9383' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bōli', 'glass')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">玻璃</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=7586' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bēi', 'cup')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">杯</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1141' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'háishì', 'still / nevertheless')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">还是</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9384' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cí', 'china / porcelain')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">瓷</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=7586' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bēi', 'cup')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">杯</a>？(Would you like a glass or a porcelain cup?) The terms 
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9383' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bōli', 'glass')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">玻璃</a> (glass) and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9384' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cí', 'china / porcelain')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">瓷</a> (porcelain) 
        act as the attributives and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=7586' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bēi', 'cup')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">杯</a> (cup) is the modified word.
      </p>
