      <p>
        Conjunctions connect two words, phrases, or sentences expressing coordination, cause and effect,
        circumstances, or conjecture. 
        Conjunctions indicating coordination include 
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=387' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'hé', 'and')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">和</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=2021' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'gēn', 'and')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">跟</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=1301' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'tóng', 'like / same / similar / together')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">同</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=509' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǔ', 'and')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">与</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=961' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jí', 'to reach')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">及</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=346' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bìng', 'and / furthermore / also')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">并</a>、and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">而</a>.
        Conjunctions indicating cause and effect include 
