      <p>
        Structural particles are added to words or phrases to express a grammatical relation.
        The structural particles are <a href='/word_detail.php?id=273' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'de', 'possessive / particle')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">的</a>，<a href='/word_detail.php?id=803' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'dì', 'earth / ground / place')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">地</a> and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=411' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'de', 'a sentence particle used after a verb to show effect / degree or possibility')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">得</a>.
        The structural particle <a href='/word_detail.php?id=273' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'de', 'possessive particle')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">的</a> can only be placed after an attributive modifier.
        For example, <a href='/word_detail.php?id=519' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'tā', 'she her')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">她</a><span class='hl'>的</span><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9489' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yīfu', 'clothes')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">衣服</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=654' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'hěn', 'very')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">很</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=4924' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'piàoliang', 'pretty / beautiful / elegant / polished')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">漂亮</a>。 (Her clothes are beautiful.)
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=803' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'de', 'structural particle')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">地</a> can only be placed after an adverbial adjunct.
        For example, <a href='/word_detail.php?id=519' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'tā', 'she her')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">她</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8185' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'kèkǔ', 'hardworking / assiduous')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">刻苦</a><span class='hl'>地</span><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1725' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xuéxí', 'to learn / to study')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">学习</a>。 (She studies hard.) 
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=411' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'de', 'a sentence particle used after a verb to show effect / degree or possibility')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">得</a> must be placed after a verb or adjective
        and before a complement. For example, <a href='/word_detail.php?id=519' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'tā', 'she her')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">她</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8911' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'pǎo', 'to run / to escape')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">跑</a><span class='hl'>得</span><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1181' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'kuài', 'fast / quick')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">快</a>。(She runs fast.)
      </p>
