      <p>
        Aspectual particles are placed after verbs to indicate a supplementary meaning.
        The aspectual particles are <a href='/word_detail.php?id=393' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'le', 'modal particle')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">了</a>（le），<a href='/word_detail.php?id=547' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhe', 'particle attached after verb to indicate action in progress')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">着</a>（zhe）and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=829' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'guò', 'aspectual particle')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">过</a>（guo）.  However, not all verb can be followed by <a href='/word_detail.php?id=547' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhe', 'particle attached after verb to indicate action in progress')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">着</a> and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=393' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'le', 'aspectual particle')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">了</a>. 
      </p>
